languages.English:
Mojang implements certain procedures to help protect children and their privacy including complying with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

You may need to obtain parental consent before accessing your Realms account.

If you have an older Minecraft account (you log in with your username), you need to migrate the account to a Mojang account in order to access Realms.
languages.Anglish:
Mojang brooks some means to help shield children and hir sundry such as following the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

You may need to fetch kennend's thaving before reaching your Realms reckoning.

If you have an older Minecraft reckoning (you go in with your brookername), you need to wander out the reckoning to a Mojang reckoning so as to reach Realms.
languages.Shakespearean English:
Mojang goeth certain courses to aid the guarding of children and their privacy, such as consigning to the Children’s On-line Privacie Protection Act (COPPA) and ye auld General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

Ye may need gain your mother or father's consent before attaining your Realms ticket.

If 't be true your Minecraft ticket groweth fusty—That is to say ye still sign your given name to gain entrance—ye need exchange it for a Mojang ticket, that ye might gain entrance to the Realms Theatre.
languages.Pirate Speak:
Mojang implements certain procedures t' help protect little sandcrabs and their privacy including complying with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

Ya may need t' obtain parental consent before accessin' yer Realms account.

If ye have an older Minecraft account (ye log in with yer username), ye need t' migrate the account to a Mojang account in order t' access Realms.

languages.English:
You can encrypt your messages using a secret key. Only people who know this key will be able to decrypt them. No Chat Reports will automatically decrypt all encrypted messages when a suitable key is provided and the feature is enabled.
However, be aware that encryption is not a "magic wand" kind of solution. Moderators on third-party servers can mute or ban you for sending what will appear to them as a garbled mess in chat. Futhermore, it is recommended that you generate a custom encryption key and communicate it to other people only via secure channels. Click "Learn More" to learn more about how and when you should use encryption.

languages.English:
This server requires all chat messages to be signed, which means they can be reported to Mojang, which may result in a ban from all multiplayer servers. This likely means that the server owner kept "enforce-secure-profile" enabled in the server.properties, which is the default since 1.19.1.

Click "Allow Signing" to enable message signing for this session. You can also use the safety status button in the chat screen to select the signing mode for this server.

languages.English:
Minecraft has run out of memory.

This could be caused by a bug in the game or by the Java Virtual Machine not being allocated enough memory.

To prevent level corruption, the current game has quit. We've tried to free up enough memory to let you go back to the main menu and back to playing, but this may not have worked.

Please restart the game if you see this message again.
languages.Anglish:
Minecraft has run out of inmind.

This could be made by a bug in the game or by the Java Aped Sare not being fordealt enough inmind.

To forestall breaking the world, the anward game has ended. We've fanded to free up enough inmind to let you go back to the main list and back to playing, but this may not have worked.

Kindly edstart the game if you see this writ ayen.
languages.Shakespearean English:
Minecraft wear it brave state out of memory.
 
This couldst beest didst cause by an issue in the game 'r by the Java Virtual Machine that it shall never cut from memory.
 
Than thy prevention can be in my rescue. Of mouthed graves will give thee memory; Thou by thy dial’s shady stealth mayst know.
 
Prithee, start thy game anew if thee receive fair speechless messages.
languages.Pirate Speak:
Arrgh! Yer ship has run out o' thinkin'!

This could be caused by too many barnicles on yer ship, or th' Java Virtual Machine not bein' allowed enough thinkin'.

Tah prevent the seven seas from boilin' the current ship has been scuttled. We ave tried to free up some headspace so yah can go back to th' shore, but we may be sinkin!

Yew should restart yer ship if yah see this again.
